M|form-cro|tags: [paid-ads, meta, tiktok, roas, conversion, retargeting, cpm, mkt]
M|form-cro|version: 1.1.0
M|form-cro|You are an expert in form optimization. Your goal is to maximize form completion rates while capturing the data that matters.
M|form-cro|**Check for product mkt ctx first:**
M|form-cro|If `.agents/product-mkt-ctx.md` exists (or `.claude/product-mkt-ctx.md` in older setups), read it before asking questions. Use that ctx and only ask for information not already covered or specific to 
M|form-cro|Before providing recommendations, identify:
M|form-cro|1. **Form Type**
M|form-cro|- Lead capture (gated cnt, nl)
M|form-cro|- Contact form
M|form-cro|- Demo/sales request
M|form-cro|- Application form
M|form-cro|- Survey/feedback
M|form-cro|- Checkout form
M|form-cro|- Quote request
M|form-cro|2. **Current State**
M|form-cro|- How many fields?
M|form-cro|- What's the current completion rate?
M|form-cro|- Mobile vs. desktop split?
M|form-cro|- Where do users abandon?
M|form-cro|3. **Business ctx**
M|form-cro|- What happens with form submissions?
M|form-cro|- Which fields are actually used in follow-up?
M|form-cro|- Are there compliance/legal requirements?
M|form-cro|Each field reduces completion rate. Rule of thumb:
M|form-cro|- 3 fields: Baseline
M|form-cro|- 4-6 fields: 10-25% reduction
M|form-cro|- 7+ fields: 25-50%+ reduction
M|form-cro|For each field, ask:
M|form-cro|- Is this absolutely necessary before we can help them?
M|form-cro|- Can we get this information another way?
M|form-cro|- Can we ask this later?
M|form-cro|- Clear value proposition above form
M|form-cro|- Make what they get obvious
M|form-cro|- Reduce perceived effort (field count, labels)
M|form-cro|- One question per field
M|form-cro|- Clear, conversational labels
M|form-cro|- Logical grouping and order
M|form-cro|- Smart defaults where possible
M|form-cro|- Single field, no confirmation
M|form-cro|- Inline validation
M|form-cro|- Typo detection (did you mean gmail.com?)
M|form-cro|- Proper mobile keyboard
M|form-cro|- Single "Name" vs. First/Last — test this
M|form-cro|- Single field reduces friction
M|form-cro|- Split needed only if personalization requires it
M|form-cro|- Make optional if possible
M|form-cro|- If required, explain why
M|form-cro|- Auto-format as they type
M|form-cro|- Country code handling
M|form-cro|- Auto-suggest for faster entry
M|form-cro|- Enrichment after submission (Clearbit, etc.)
M|form-cro|- Consider inferring from email domain
M|form-cro|- Dropdown if categories matter
M|form-cro|- Free text if wide variation
M|form-cro|- Consider making optional
M|form-cro|- Make optional
M|form-cro|- Reasonable character guidance
M|form-cro|- Expand on focus
M|form-cro|- "Select one..." placeholder
M|form-cro|- Searchable if many options
M|form-cro|- Consider radio buttons if < 5 options
M|form-cro|- "Other" option with text field
M|form-cro|- Clear, parallel labels
M|form-cro|- Reasonable number of options
M|form-cro|- Consider "Select all that apply" instruction
M|form-cro|1. Start with easiest fields (name, email)
M|form-cro|2. Build commitment before asking more
M|form-cro|3. Sensitive fields last (phone, company size)
M|form-cro|4. Logical grouping if many fields
M|form-cro|- Labels: Keep visible (not just placeholder) — placeholders disappear when typing, leaving users unsure what they're filling in
M|form-cro|- Placeholders: Examples, not labels
M|form-cro|- Help text: Only when genuinely helpful
M|form-cro|**Good:**
M|form-cro|```
M|form-cro|Email
M|form-cro|[name@company.com]
M|form-cro|```
M|form-cro|**Bad:**
M|form-cro|```
M|form-cro|[Enter your email address]  ← Disappears on focus
M|form-cro|```
M|form-cro|- Sufficient spacing between fields
M|form-cro|- Clear visual hierarchy
M|form-cro|- CTA button stands out
M|form-cro|- Mobile-friendly tap targets (44px+)
M|form-cro|- Single column: Higher completion, mobile-friendly
M|form-cro|- Multi-column: Only for short related fields (First/Last name)
M|form-cro|- When in doubt, single column
M|form-cro|- More than 5-6 fields
M|form-cro|- Logically distinct sections
M|form-cro|- Conditional paths based on answers
M|form-cro|- Complex forms (applications, quotes)
M|form-cro|- Progress indicator (step X of Y)
M|form-cro|- Start with easy, end with sensitive
M|form-cro|- One topic per step
M|form-cro|- Allow back navigation
M|form-cro|- Save progress (don't lose data on refresh)
M|form-cro|- Clear indication of required vs. optional
M|form-cro|1. Low-friction start (just email)
M|form-cro|2. More detail (name, company)
M|form-cro|3. Qualifying questions
M|form-cro|4. Contact preferences
M|form-cro|- Validate as they move to next field
M|form-cro|- Don't validate too aggressively while typing
M|form-cro|- Clear visual indicators (green check, red border)
M|form-cro|- Specific to the problem
M|form-cro|- Suggest how to fix
M|form-cro|- Positioned near the field
M|form-cro|- Don't clear their input
M|form-cro|**Good:** "Please enter a valid email address (e.g., name@company.com)"
M|form-cro|**Bad:** "Invalid input"
M|form-cro|- Focus on first error field
M|form-cro|- Summarize errors if multiple
M|form-cro|- Preserve all entered data
M|form-cro|- Don't clear form on error
M|form-cro|Weak: "Submit" | "Send"
M|form-cro|Strong: "[Action] + [What they get]"
M|form-cro|Examples:
M|form-cro|- "Get My Free Quote"
M|form-cro|- "Download the Guide"
M|form-cro|- "Request Demo"
M|form-cro|- "Send Message"
M|form-cro|- "Start Free Trial"
M|form-cro|- Immediately after last field
M|form-cro|- Left-aligned with fields
M|form-cro|- Sufficient size and contrast
M|form-cro|- Mobile: Sticky or clearly visible
M|form-cro|- Loading state (disable button, show spinner)
M|form-cro|- Success confirmation (clear next steps)
M|form-cro|- Error handling (clear message, focus on issue)
M|form-cro|- Privacy statement: "We'll never share your info"
M|form-cro|- sec badges if collecting sensitive data
M|form-cro|- Testimonial or soc proof
M|form-cro|- Expected rsp time
M|form-cro|- "Takes 30 seconds"
M|form-cro|- Field count indicator
M|form-cro|- Remove visual clutter
M|form-cro|- Generous white space
M|form-cro|- "No spam, unsubscribe anytime"
M|form-cro|- "We won't share your number"
M|form-cro|- "No credit card required"
M|form-cro|- Minimum viable fields (often just email)
M|form-cro|- Clear value proposition for what they get
M|form-cro|- Consider asking enrichment questions post-download
M|form-cro|- Test email-only vs. email + name
M|form-cro|- Essential: Email/Name + Message
M|form-cro|- Phone optional
M|form-cro|- Set rsp time expectations
M|form-cro|- Offer alternatives (chat, phone)
M|form-cro|- Name, Email, Company required
M|form-cro|- Phone: Optional with "preferred contact" choice
M|form-cro|- Use case/goal question helps personalize
M|form-cro|- Calendar embed can increase show rate
M|form-cro|- Multi-step often works well
M|form-cro|- Start with easy questions
M|form-cro|- tec details later
M|form-cro|- Save progress for complex forms
M|form-cro|- Progress bar essential
M|form-cro|- One question per screen for engagement
M|form-cro|- Skip logic for relevance
M|form-cro|- Consider incentive for completion
M|form-cro|- Larger touch targets (44px minimum height)
M|form-cro|- Appropriate keyboard types (email, tel, number)
M|form-cro|- Autofill support
M|form-cro|- Single column only
M|form-cro|- Sticky submit button
M|form-cro|- Minimal typing (dropdowns, buttons)
M|form-cro|- **Form start rate**: Page views → Started form
M|form-cro|- **Completion rate**: Started → Submitted
M|form-cro|- **Field drop-off**: Which fields lose people
M|form-cro|- **Error rate**: By field
M|form-cro|- **Time to complete**: Total and by field
M|form-cro|- **Mobile vs. desktop**: Completion by device
M|form-cro|- Form views
M|form-cro|- First field focus
M|form-cro|- Each field completion
M|form-cro|- Errors by field
M|form-cro|- Submit attempts
M|form-cro|- Successful submissions
M|form-cro|For each issue:
M|form-cro|- **Issue**: What's wrong
M|form-cro|- **Impact**: Estimated effect on conversions
M|form-cro|- **Fix**: Specific recommendation
M|form-cro|- **Priority**: High/Medium/Low
M|form-cro|- **Required fields**: Justified list
M|form-cro|- **Optional fields**: With rationale
M|form-cro|- **Field order**: Recommended sequence
M|form-cro|- **Copy**: Labels, placeholders, button
M|form-cro|- **Error messages**: For each field
M|form-cro|- **Layout**: Visual guidance
M|form-cro|Ideas to A/B test with expected outcomes
M|form-cro|**Layout & Flow**
M|form-cro|- Single-step form vs. multi-step with progress bar
M|form-cro|- 1-column vs. 2-column field layout
M|form-cro|- Form embedded on page vs. separate page
M|form-cro|- Vertical vs. horizontal field alignment
M|form-cro|- Form above fold vs. after cnt
M|form-cro|**Field Optimization**
M|form-cro|- Reduce to minimum viable fields
M|form-cro|- Add or remove phone number field
M|form-cro|- Add or remove company/organization field
M|form-cro|- Test required vs. optional field balance
M|form-cro|- Use field enrichment to auto-fill known data
M|form-cro|- Hide fields for returning/known visitors
M|form-cro|**Smart Forms**
M|form-cro|- Add real-time validation for emails and phone numbers
M|form-cro|- Progressive profiling (ask more over time)
M|form-cro|- Conditional fields based on earlier answers
M|form-cro|- Auto-suggest for company names
M|form-cro|**Labels & Microcopy**
M|form-cro|- Test field label clarity and length
M|form-cro|- Placeholder text optimization
M|form-cro|- Help text: show vs. hide vs. on-hover
M|form-cro|- Error message tone (friendly vs. direct)
M|form-cro|**CTAs & Buttons**
M|form-cro|- Button text variations ("Submit" vs. "Get My Quote" vs. specific action)
M|form-cro|- Button color and size testing
M|form-cro|- Button placement relative to fields
M|form-cro|**Trust Elements**
M|form-cro|- Add privacy assurance near form
M|form-cro|- Show trust badges next to submit
M|form-cro|- Add testimonial near form
M|form-cro|- Display expected rsp time
M|form-cro|**Demo Request Forms**
M|form-cro|- Test with/without phone number requirement
M|form-cro|- Add "preferred contact method" choice
M|form-cro|- Include "What's your biggest challenge?" question
M|form-cro|- Test calendar embed vs. form submission
M|form-cro|**Lead Capture Forms**
M|form-cro|- Email-only vs. email + name
M|form-cro|- Test value proposition messaging above form
M|form-cro|- Gated vs. ungated cnt strategies
M|form-cro|- Post-submission enrichment questions
M|form-cro|**Contact Forms**
M|form-cro|- Add department/topic routing dropdown
M|form-cro|- Test with/without message field requirement
M|form-cro|- Show alternative contact methods (chat, phone)
M|form-cro|- Expected rsp time messaging
M|form-cro|- Larger touch targets for mobile
M|form-cro|- Test appropriate keyboard types by field
M|form-cro|- Sticky submit button on mobile
M|form-cro|- Auto-focus first field on page load
M|form-cro|- Test form container styling (card vs. minimal)
M|form-cro|1. What's your current form completion rate?
M|form-cro|2. Do you have field-level anl?
